# `README.md` at repository root

When this is the **top-level** `README.md` (repo root, not a nested `builds/<build-dir>/README.md`):

- Aim at **people using** the builds (install, `./wsl-builder.sh`, build list, tips).
- Do **not** add maintainer wiring, dispatch/source-order details, or agent-only instructions—those live in `.cursor/rules/`.
- Do **not** add meta lines about how the README or table is structured (e.g. “one row per build”, “bold means components”). Use **headings and column headers** only for users; table conventions for agents are in [bash-component-patterns.mdc](bash-component-patterns.mdc) (**Repo root Build List**).
- **Build List (root README only):** follow the checklist in [bash-component-patterns.mdc](bash-component-patterns.mdc) § **Repo root Build List**—columns, ordering (substantive before QoL), **Additional Conf** (`<br/>`, ~30-char lines, no token splits). For nested `builds/<name>/README.md`, ignore this Build List section.
